topicSummary: Baker's cysts (also known as popliteal cysts) are not true cysts. They are a distension of the gastrocnemius-semimembranosus bursa behind the knee.

topicHtmlObjects.htmlHeader: Baker's cyst: Summary

latestChanges.title: Reviewed
latestChanges.body: A literature search was conducted in February 2016 to identify evidence-based guidelines, UK policy, systematic reviews, and key randomized controlled trials published since the last revision of this topic. No major changes to recommendations have been made.
